    {
      "id": 808228,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "Due to uninitialized data in a network packet, a memory address was leaked in Mario Kart World. This allowed an attacker to bypass ASLR, which is a prerequisite for many kinds of attacks. The vulnerability was fixed in Mario Kart World version 1.5.0.",
